# Hub controller-installation and configuration

1. Make sure the current hub-controller is stopped 

	- sudo systemctl stop controller.service
	- sudo systemctl stop controller_web.service
	- go to <app_path>/hub-controller/bin and sudo ./uninstall
	
2. remove the current hub-controller directory on hub
3. copy the latest hub-controller zip file to the hub to /to home directory of vesta
4. copy the hub-controller zip file to the <app_path>
5. unzip the hub-controller zip file and go to hub-controller folder and run -> sudo ./insatll.sh

# Octopus-installation and configuration

1. Make sure the current octopus is stopped 

	- go to <app_path>/octopus-1.2.8/bin and ./stop
	- check the status by ./status

		        or

	- sudo systemctl stop octopus.service

2. remove the current octopus directory on hub
3. copy the latest octopus zip and octopus.service to the hub to home directory of vesta
4. copy the octopus zip file to the <app_path>
5. copy the octopus.service file to the /lib/systemd/system/ 
6. makesure to remove the .m2 file in the root before unzip
7. unzip the octopus file
	
## octopus-Configurations

    # check the internal guild
	

Once configurations are done ->

8. reload the daemon - > sudo systemctl daemon-reload
9. enable the octopus service - >  sudo systemctl enable octopus.service
10. start the octopus service - >  sudo systemctl start octopus.service
11. check octopus status - > sudo systemctl status octopus.service
